00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
What are the stages of application for procurement?

00:05.000 --> 00:12.000
Let's take a closer look at the stages of application for procurement.

00:12.000 --> 00:18.000
As I have already noted, one of the first and most important stages is the approval of specifications.

00:18.000 --> 00:30.000
From my personal experience, I can tell you that very often there are situations when the procurement department employee and the internal customer,

00:30.000 --> 00:38.000
the person or department that applies for the purchase of a particular material, do not agree with their actions.

00:38.000 --> 00:55.000
As a result, the purchased equipment, goods, and even services do not always meet the expectations of the customer.

00:56.000 --> 01:12.000
Therefore, one of the main priorities in the procurement process is a clear understanding that what the internal customer wants and what the procurement department acquires is the same.

01:12.000 --> 01:26.000
On the other hand, there are very often situations when the internal customer does not know what models of equipment exist on the market,

01:26.000 --> 01:42.000
and the procurement department manager's task is to explain, show the market, show the general picture to the customer,

01:42.000 --> 01:49.000
in order to help him make the right choice, write the specification, and so on.

01:50.000 --> 01:56.000
After the approval of the specifications, the phase of choosing suppliers begins.

01:56.000 --> 02:01.000
What actions are included in this phase?

02:01.000 --> 02:07.000
It is obvious that there is no unique search strategy.

02:08.000 --> 02:20.000
Someone uses a yellow-page magazine, someone searches the Internet, someone has established connections for years, someone uses acquaintances.

02:21.000 --> 02:36.000
This is one of the most difficult and serious phases, because the entire result of the procurement service depends on the supplier.

02:37.000 --> 02:51.000
Here you need to assess not only the financial stability, not only the time the supplier exists and works on the market,

02:51.000 --> 03:04.000
but also assess the future prospects, how long and how seriously this supplier can work with you in the future.

03:05.000 --> 03:08.000
There is a concept of strategic suppliers.

03:08.000 --> 03:24.000
Often, companies that provide raw materials or very expensive equipment or services are referred to this category of suppliers.

03:25.000 --> 03:33.000
A strategic supplier can be referred to as an oil refinery and an oil supplier.

03:33.000 --> 03:43.000
In this case, the oil supplier will be a strategic supplier, because the plant has a continuous cycle.

03:44.000 --> 03:54.000
It is vital to have stable supplies so that the production cycle does not stop.

03:54.000 --> 04:04.000
There are different strategies for finding suppliers for the effective use of the procurement resources.

04:04.000 --> 04:18.000
Some companies that do not compete in one industry unite to strengthen the purchasing power.

04:18.000 --> 04:27.000
By uniting the volumes of purchases, companies claim more favorable supply conditions.

04:27.000 --> 04:42.000
One of the latest examples is the unification of a large and well-known e-commerce network in Russia with a large network in Ukraine.

04:42.000 --> 05:03.000
By uniting their orders, these two companies, without competing in their markets, achieved a 5% discount on the purchase of a certain brand of household electronics.

05:03.000 --> 05:09.000
We have already discussed prices and supply conditions.

05:09.000 --> 05:15.000
Now let's talk about price quotas.

05:15.000 --> 05:17.000
What are price quotas?

05:17.000 --> 05:27.000
Price quotas are offers and conditions that are received from the supplier to the procurement department.

05:28.000 --> 05:37.000
Usually, price quotas describe conditions, supply, place, quantity.

05:37.000 --> 06:00.000
After receiving these documents, the company employees, not only the procurement department employees, but also the internal customers, have a difficult task to determine the fair price of the purchase.

06:00.000 --> 06:07.000
I would like to note that very often the lowest price is understood as the best.

06:07.000 --> 06:13.000
But from experience, I would say that this is not always the case.

06:13.000 --> 06:20.000
You need to look at the overall factors and what the company gets in the end, having paid a certain price.

06:20.000 --> 06:30.000
The so-called cost of the product and what value this product, purchased at a certain price, will bring to the company.

06:30.000 --> 06:40.000
Therefore, the factors that are taken into account when making a decision are, of course, the price, quality, and supply conditions.

06:40.000 --> 06:51.000
The possibility of constant and timely, uninterrupted delivery.

06:51.000 --> 07:06.000
And one very important factor is the service, after-sale service, the overall level of cooperation, the exchange of documents, the exchange of information.

07:07.000 --> 07:15.000
These conditions are the basis for making a decision.

07:15.000 --> 07:26.000
To adopt a strategy for purchasing, the procurement department manager must take all the above factors as a guide to action.

07:26.000 --> 07:33.000
After a potential supplier is determined, the phase of receiving the product to the warehouse comes.

07:33.000 --> 07:41.000
It is certainly very important where and in what condition the product you have purchased will end up.

07:41.000 --> 07:49.000
The specialist in receiving the product to the warehouse, in our understanding, is often called a storekeeper,

07:49.000 --> 07:59.000
must notify the procurement service about the product received, what application the product was accepted for,

07:59.000 --> 08:12.000
whether the quantity, quality, packaging, marking, additional conditions correspond to those that were declared by the internal client or internal customer.

08:12.000 --> 08:19.000
As soon as the procurement manager receives information about the availability of the product, the payment phase for the received product begins.

08:19.000 --> 08:26.000
The payment phase for the received product is called the pre-payment phase.

08:26.000 --> 08:33.000
The role of the procurement service specialist is to monitor the timely payment,

08:33.000 --> 08:41.000
since we are responsible to the supplier for the fulfillment of our obligations.

08:41.000 --> 08:53.000
Summing up the work of the procurement department, it should be noted that in fact it is one of the most specific,

08:53.000 --> 09:00.000
one of the most complex functions that are included in the entire delivery system.

09:00.000 --> 09:12.000
It is no secret that this is the department where there are abuse, violations of corporate ethics, violations of business ethics.

09:12.000 --> 09:21.000
Therefore, one of the key tasks, and I would say the most important task, is to select the personnel,

09:22.000 --> 09:31.000
to select the personnel for the delivery system in general and specifically for the procurement department.

