Inbound logistics.

09:35.000 --> 09:46.000
Traditionally, inbound logistics is associated with the process of purchasing and delivering materials to the warehouse.

09:46.000 --> 09:57.000
Obtaining and storing raw materials is the first and main part of the entire logistics process.

09:57.000 --> 10:03.000
Some researchers consider the inbound logistics to be a fairly limited function,

10:03.000 --> 10:12.000
which includes elements such as purchasing and transporting goods to the warehouse.

10:13.000 --> 10:19.000
I would like to note the difference between inbound and outbound logistics.

10:19.000 --> 10:28.000
Since outbound logistics is a subject of its activity,

10:28.000 --> 10:33.000
