11:04.000 --> 11:12.000
he makes his requirements to the organization for packaging, for the completion of the finished product,

11:12.000 --> 11:26.000
while the inbound logistics operates with the material or raw material that does not require such a careful approach to the selection of the equipment as the outbound logistics require.

11:26.000 --> 11:32.000
The second difference is the very essence of the transported goods.

11:32.000 --> 11:40.000
The material specialist who is part of the purchasing service in the inbound logistics phase

11:40.000 --> 11:48.000
works mainly with large masses of raw materials and components.

11:48.000 --> 12:00.000
In addition, the raw materials have other requirements for transportation, storage, than the finished product,

12:00.000 --> 12:06.000
