16:21.000 --> 16:23.000
What is transport?

16:23.000 --> 16:28.000
When transporting raw materials and finished products,

16:28.000 --> 16:34.000
it is usually meant to move goods from one point to another geographically.

16:34.000 --> 16:42.000
This is the element that constitutes the delivery system as one of the most capital-intensive.

16:42.000 --> 16:49.000
The importance of this function is evidenced by the fact that almost at every enterprise

16:49.000 --> 16:54.000
there is a position or a person who is responsible for the transport.

16:54.000 --> 17:00.000
In the context of the procurement service or the delivery system,

17:00.000 --> 17:04.000
regardless of how the transport is used,

17:04.000 --> 17:08.000
either it is a third-party company providing services,

17:08.000 --> 17:12.000
or there is its own transport department or site,

17:12.000 --> 17:21.000
there is always a person or a function that controls the transportation of materials from one point to another.

17:21.000 --> 17:24.000
The transportation of materials is a service,

17:24.000 --> 17:27.000
but regardless of the fact that it is a service,

17:27.000 --> 17:31.000
the acquisition of this service is comparable to the acquisition of materials.

17:31.000 --> 17:39.000
One of the aspects of transportation is, in essence, a service for moving goods.

17:39.000 --> 17:42.000
This aspect includes the main indicators,

17:43.000 --> 17:51.000
speed, reliability and frequency of movement and delivery of this service.

17:51.000 --> 17:55.000
The next important factor is the type of transport.

17:55.000 --> 18:01.000
Traditionally, five types of transport are distinguished.

18:01.000 --> 18:09.000
1. Pipe transport. It is used for liquid and gas-like products, such as oil, gas, water.

18:09.000 --> 18:17.000
2. Air transport. In theory, any type of product can be transported by air,

18:17.000 --> 18:20.000
but there are certain restrictions.

18:20.000 --> 18:24.000
These are in terms of quantity, weight, size.

18:24.000 --> 18:30.000
Accordingly, air transport is one of the most expensive, if not the most expensive.

18:30.000 --> 18:31.000
3. Water transport.

18:31.000 --> 18:38.000
Its significant difference is that it also allows you to transport almost any material.

18:38.000 --> 18:44.000
It allows you to transport large-sized materials,

18:44.000 --> 18:51.000
but there are restrictions due to low speed and geographical restrictions,

18:51.000 --> 18:58.000
since not every point has access to a sea or river port.

18:58.000 --> 19:04.000
4. Railway transport. Along with car transport, it is one of the most used.

19:04.000 --> 19:13.000
It allows you to transport large volumes of goods, large dimensions, high delivery speed,

19:13.000 --> 19:17.000
but there are also restrictions on the location,

19:17.000 --> 19:22.000
since there are not railway routes and terminals laid everywhere.

19:23.000 --> 19:28.000
Railway transport is often combined with other types of transport.

19:28.000 --> 19:34.000
5. Automobile transport. Automobile transport is one of the most popular and often used.

19:34.000 --> 19:46.000
Because the roads are laid on a large area, this type of transport is used most often.

19:46.000 --> 19:51.000
It allows you to transport both small and large volumes of goods,

19:51.000 --> 19:57.000
but at the same time there are restrictions on the use of this type of transport,

19:57.000 --> 20:02.000
due to the fact that there are restrictions on dimensions,

20:02.000 --> 20:09.000
and, especially due to the growing prices for energy carriers,

20:09.000 --> 20:13.000
the cost of this type of transport is significantly increased.

20:13.000 --> 20:19.000
It is obvious that depending on the type of transport, the type of transport is chosen.

20:19.000 --> 20:24.000
