25:30.000 --> 25:34.000
The issue of production organization is quite complex.

25:34.000 --> 25:38.000
Traditional operational management of enterprises

25:38.000 --> 25:42.000
is associated with the production of a particular product.

25:42.000 --> 25:48.000
However, in fact, the same principles apply to any type of business,

25:48.000 --> 25:52.000
from production to service.

25:52.000 --> 25:58.000
The decision on how to produce a product or service

25:58.000 --> 26:01.000
is formed by your operational strategy.

26:01.000 --> 26:03.000
What will you choose?

26:03.000 --> 26:06.000
Production in-stock, production on order,

26:06.000 --> 26:11.000
specific production development, or a combination of these options?

26:11.000 --> 26:15.000
Maybe you will use the services of a third-party organization

26:15.000 --> 26:18.000
to produce your main product?

26:18.000 --> 26:22.000
Maybe you will choose production in another country

26:22.000 --> 26:25.000
with subsequent delivery to your warehouse?

26:25.000 --> 26:28.000
Where will a particular product be produced?

26:28.000 --> 26:36.000
Where will the initial and final phase of production cycle be?

26:36.000 --> 26:39.000
The solution to these issues is critical

26:39.000 --> 26:44.000
due to their impact on the final cost of the finished product.

26:44.000 --> 26:48.000
It forms the entire system structure,

26:48.000 --> 26:55.000
and its purpose is to support the production cycle,

26:55.000 --> 26:59.000
regardless of whether it is a bank, a transport company,

26:59.000 --> 27:02.000
a production company or a producer.

27:02.000 --> 27:06.000
Your production and operational strategy

27:06.000 --> 27:13.000
directly affects the function and strategy of the delivery system.

27:13.000 --> 27:20.000
Let's talk about the above-mentioned production strategies.

27:20.000 --> 27:25.000
One of the most common is production in-stock.

27:25.000 --> 27:29.000
This strategy is used for products

27:29.000 --> 27:36.000
with a low level of variety of designs and forms.

27:36.000 --> 27:43.000
It is best suited for standard products produced in large volumes.

27:43.000 --> 27:46.000
The larger the volume of the produced batches,

27:46.000 --> 27:51.000
the lower the cost of the final product.

27:51.000 --> 27:54.000
The advantage of this system is that,

27:54.000 --> 27:59.000
by producing a product and storing it in a warehouse,

27:59.000 --> 28:03.000
the speed of response to customer requests increases.

28:03.000 --> 28:07.000
If you receive an order for a particular type of product,

28:07.000 --> 28:10.000
you can immediately unload it.

28:10.000 --> 28:12.000
Production in-stock.

28:12.000 --> 28:15.000
This strategy is preferred for products

28:15.000 --> 28:19.000
produced in standard design and form,

28:19.000 --> 28:26.000
but with the purpose of satisfying specific customer requirements.

28:26.000 --> 28:29.000
The following strategies are used by companies

28:29.000 --> 28:35.000
that produce products only when the customer has an order.

28:35.000 --> 28:41.000
This allows them to maintain a low level of stock of finished products

28:41.000 --> 28:46.000
and goods and to produce a wide range of products at the same time.

28:46.000 --> 28:50.000
A typical example of this strategy is car production.

28:51.000 --> 28:56.000
The way companies sell and produce cars

28:56.000 --> 29:03.000
is that at a certain time,

29:03.000 --> 29:10.000
the car distributor sends an order to the factory,

29:10.000 --> 29:15.000
where the car brands are written,

29:15.000 --> 29:20.000
their configuration, up to the color and so on.

29:20.000 --> 29:25.000
The factory manufacturer, having received this order,

29:25.000 --> 29:30.000
already forms its production cycle and production schedule.

29:30.000 --> 29:36.000
Thus, exactly the number of cars that were ordered is unloaded,

29:36.000 --> 29:42.000
and the unsold cars are not accumulated in the warehouse.

29:42.000 --> 29:44.000
Ordering.

29:44.000 --> 29:51.000
Ordering is a mixed strategy that allows you to produce a series of products,

29:51.000 --> 29:56.000
but the final preparation and adjustment

29:56.000 --> 30:01.000
is done for each customer separately upon receiving the order.

30:01.000 --> 30:06.000
This strategy is usually used for those types of products

30:06.000 --> 30:08.000
when a wide range is produced,

30:08.000 --> 30:13.000
but companies need to maintain low warehouse reserves.

30:13.000 --> 30:19.000
An example is the production of souvenir products

30:19.000 --> 30:22.000
or products with the customer's logo.

30:22.000 --> 30:25.000
When planning an advertising campaign,

30:25.000 --> 30:33.000
the company may want to put the logo of its organization on a standard pen.

30:33.000 --> 30:38.000
In this case, the factory manufacturer can store the pens of a standard type,

30:38.000 --> 30:40.000
a standard shape in its warehouse,

30:40.000 --> 30:48.000
but put the logo of a specific customer who orders this type of service.

30:48.000 --> 30:51.000
And work on the order.

30:51.000 --> 30:55.000
Usually, this strategy is used by companies

30:55.000 --> 31:00.000
